## 3. Conformity Assessment

{% set v = verdict.verdict %}
{% if "HIGH_RISK" in v or "High-Risk" in v %}
### For High-Risk AI Systems (Annex IV)

The following obligations apply to this system under Regulation (EU) 2024/1689:

- **Article 9** – Risk management system must be established and maintained throughout the lifecycle
- **Article 10** – Training, validation, and test data must meet quality criteria; bias must be examined
- **Article 11** – Technical documentation (Annex IV) must be kept up to date
- **Article 13** – System must provide adequate transparency and instructions for use
- **Article 14** – Appropriate human oversight measures must be implemented
- **Article 15** – Accuracy, robustness and cybersecurity must be ensured
- **Third-party conformity assessment** may be required before market placement (Article 43)

#### Required Annex IV Documentation Elements

1. A detailed description of the elements of the AI system and the process for its development, including the methods and steps used
2. Detailed information about the monitoring, functioning and control of the AI system
3. Description of the risk management system established under Article 9
4. A description of any changes made to the system throughout its lifecycle
5. A list of harmonised standards applied in full or in part
6. EU declaration of conformity as referred to in Article 47
7. Post-market monitoring plan in accordance with Article 72
8. Serious incidents log in accordance with Article 73

